definition.value: A glycosyl glycoside derivative consisting of a 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residue and a D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1<->1) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl glycoside D-xylopyraonse and D-glucopyranose joined by a (1<->1) glycosidic linkage.
A glycosyl glycoside consisting of a D-glucopyranose residue and a D-galactopyranose residue joined by a (1<->1) glycosidic bond.
A prenol phosphate comprising (2E)-4-hydroxy-3-methylbut-2-en-1-ol having an O-diphosphate substituent.
